	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here is the list of stuff you need to make it...<br><br>you must get an enchanter to imbue 3 (less for other pieces) bricks of adamantite.  Once that is done, combine a brick, a file, and a neriak nectar to make an imbued adamantite ring.  Do this two more times for a total of three rings.  This part MUST be done at the Teir'Dal forge in Neriak Third Gate.  Then you have an enchanter (or shaman) friend buy you a sapphire (it's a lot cheaper if they buy it) and give it to a DEF cleric to imbue the stone.<br><br>First go kill some non-Dark elves until you get some Elf Blood.  Then go to a Shadow Man camp and kill them for some Essence of Shadow.  Once you have a hand full of each, return to neriak, and find a brew barrel.  Combine 1 elf blood, 2 essence of shadow, and 1 neriak nectar, to get a Shadow Temper.  The shadow temper uses your brewing skill, and is trivial at level 135.<br><br>Then go get some spider silks and make a silk swatch by combining them two at a time (tailoring skill, trivial at a very low level).<br><br>Go to Neriak Third Gate, and go to the merchant selling the racial smithing materials.  Buy however many bricks you need (depending on piece), the appropriate pattern, and a Teir'Dal Smithy Hammer.  Next you must get an enchanter to imbue 3 (less for other pieces) bricks of adamantite.  Once that is done, combine a brick, a file, and a neriak nectar to make an imbued adamantite ring.  Do this two more times for a total of three rings.  This part MUST be done at the Teir'Dal forge in Neriak Third Gate.  It HAS to be a Dark Elf Inny worshipper.  Then you have an enchanter (or shaman) friend buy you a sapphire (it's a lot cheaper if they buy it) and give it to a DEF cleric to imbue the stone.<br><br>Now, put in your enchanted adamantite rings, shadow temper, silk swatch, pattern, and TD smith hammer in the forge, hit combine, and voila...<br><br>There is your Imbued Teir'Dal Chainmail Tunic (assuming you have a sufficient smithing skill).  Just as a warning, non-imbued for me fails about 50% of the time, and I have a skill of 175.  I hear that the imbued is harder to make, so I am waiting until my skill is higher.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
